    "title": "Assistant Store Manager - Decathlon India - 2025 Hiring Drive",
    "description": "If you're a passionate Assistant Store Manager with drive and ambition, Decathlon India in Coimbatore is the place for you. We're growing fast and need talented people to grow with us.\n\nAbout Decathlon India:\nDecathlon India is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Coordinate with the supply chain team for timely stock delivery\n• Manage store operations to ensure smooth daily functioning\n• Implement promotional activities and in-store campaigns\n• Conduct regular stock audits and prevent pilferage\n• Achieve sales targets and improve store performance metrics\n• Handle customer queries, complaints, and escalations effectively\n• Manage shrinkage and reduce stock discrepancies\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Any graduate with relevant experience\n• 0-1 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in E-commerce Integration\n• Proficiency in Team Leadership\n• Proficiency in Customer Service\n• Proficiency in Omnichannel Retail\n• Proficiency in Supply Chain\n• Proficiency in KPI Management\n• Proficiency in Category Management\n• Proficiency in Retail Analytics\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Maternity and paternity leave\n• Annual performance appraisal\n• Employee stock options (ESOPs) for eligible roles\n• Transportation and conveyance allowance\n• Flexible working hours\n• Life and accident insurance\n• Salary Range: 2.5 LPA - 6 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Coimbatore, Tamil Nadu, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Decathlon India!",
